 Former Arsenal midfielder Alex Song sets up a construction company in Cameroon. The 33-year-old spent seven seasons with Premier League giant where he featured 204 times and scored 10 goals before departing for Barcelona on 20 August 2012 Song recently won the 2020-21 Djibouti Premier League title with AS Arta Solar 7 took his social media handle to share pictures of building work and artists’ impressions of his planned apartment block in home town Douala. Former Cameroon international Song has also opened a Canadian international school and College in Douala last October. Song featured in two Africa Cup of Nations and two FIFA World Cup in his 49 appearances before hanging international career aged 27, citing his wish to focus on rebuilding his domestic career with West Ham. Post Views: 
